DESCRIPTION

	A Raft consensus algorithm implementation for [ESP-C3] microcontrollers family
	(specifically, ESP32-C3FN4) written in [Zig]. This project shows distributed
	leader election across multiple [ESP-C3] boards using the [Raft] protocol.

	Each board participates in the voting process and uses a single LED indicator
	to visually display its current state in the cluster:

		* Follower: slow blinking.
		* Candidate: quick blinking.
		* Leader: static lightning.
		* Invalid: no lightning.

	Communication between nodes is handled via [ESP-NOW], a connectionless
	protocol that leverages the [ESP32-C3]'s built-in WiFi capabilities for
	fast, low-power peer-to-peer messaging without requiring a router or
	access point.

	This serves as both a practical example of implementing [Raft] on
	resource-constrained embedded systems and a visual demonstration of
	distributed consensus in action. Multiple boards can be networked
	together to form a fault-tolerant cluster where leadership automatically
	transitions if the current leader fails.

	This project has no external dependencies beyond [ESP-NOW]. The [Raft]
	implementation and all supporting code are written from scratch in [Zig]
	without relying on third-party libraries or packages.

REQUIREMENTS

	* [Zig] (`0.15`).
	* [CMake] (`3.31`).
	* [GAS] (`2.45`).
	* [LD] (`2.45`).
	* [IDF] (`5.5`).

